                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/509: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-28T13:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1927—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 28—9:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>268. Following received from American consul, Amoy: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 27, noon. Your March 25, noon, and March 25, 8 p.m. I have
                            notified Americans [to] concentrate at Amoy. Local conditions quiet at
                            present. Twenty-one Americans returning to Foochow left steamer at Amoy,
                            March 25th, on my advice Price agreeing, but five, including Bishop
                            Brown particularly, today have decided to proceed. Japanese warship
                            here, British warship expected to arrive. Believe that settlement is
                            safe as long as naval forces are present.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
